  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 2.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The chief",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The word here used means the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "corner-stones",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of a building. Hence it is applied to the chief men, who, as it were, bind and keep together the whole people. Their presence at this great meeting is mentioned to show that it was a regularly constituted assembly of all Israel. The same phrase occurs ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 14:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 19:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "stay of the tribes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.). The numbers (400,000) are of course those of the whole congregation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": ". The assembly of the people of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". So, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 16:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 20:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Israel is called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the congregation of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "congregation of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Not dissimilar was the first great council of the Church, consisting of the Church (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἡ ἐκελησια",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the assembly of disciples) and the apostles and elders (who were the cornerstones, the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "lapides angulares",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", thereof). See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 15:4, 6, 12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Four hundred thousand",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See ver. 17. The enumeration in the wilderness gave 603,550 (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 2:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 11:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and at the second numbering 601,730 (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 26:51",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 11:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a general assembly of the whole people, summoned by sending a piece of the flesh of a yoke of oxen \"throughout all the coasts of Israel,\" amounted to 330,000. David's numbering gave of Israel 800,000, and of Judah 500,000, in all 1,300,000; but these were not assembled together, but numbered at their own homes. Jehoshaphat's men of war amounted to 1,160,000 according to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 17:14-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the time of Amaziah there were of Judah alone 300,000 men able to go forth to war (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 24:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Judges 20:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
